'''Sherwin Campbell Badger''' (August 29, 1901 &ndash; April 8, 1972) was an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]] who competed in singles and pairs. He earned the men's titles at the [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships]] from 1920 through 1924. He also captured the pairs gold medal with partner [[Beatrix Loughran]] three times, and the pair won the silver medal at the [[1932 Winter Olympics]]. Prior to pairing with Loughran, he competed first with [[Clara Frothingham]] and later with [[Edith Rotch]].
After his competitive career ended, he was a skating judge and the head of the [[U.S. Figure Skating Association]]. He was born in [[Boston, Massachusetts]], and died in [[Sherborn, Massachusetts]].
